uhammad (2005). An Army, its Role and Rule: A History of the Pakistan Army from Independence to Kargil 1947\u20131999. Pittsburgh: RoseDog Books. {{ISBN|0-8059-9594-3}}.\n\n== External links ==\n{{Wikiquote}}\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20171010093717/http://www.dailymotion.com/video/x138s7i_zia-ul-haq-biography-shaheed-e-islam_news Biography video 'Shaheed e Islam]\n* [http://alsos.wlu.edu/qsearch.aspx?browse=people/Zia-ul-Haq,+Mohammad Annotated Bibliography for Muhammad Zia-ul-Haq from the Alsos Digital Library for Nuclear Issues]\n* [http://www.edwardjayepstein.com/archived/zia.htm \"Who Killed Zia?\"] by Edward Jay Epstein for ''[[Vanity Fair (magazine)|Vanity Fair]]'', September 1989\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20100824194016/http://www.pakistanarmy.gov.pk/AWPReview/TextContent.aspx?pId=150 Official profile at Pakistan Army website]\n* [http://www.pakistani.org/pakistan/constitution/ The Constitution of the Islamic Republic of Pakistan]\n* [http://www.timesonline.co.uk/tol/news/world/asia/article4543628.ece General Zia-ul-Haq's plane crash due to mechanical problem (Times of London)]\n* [https://www.britannica.com/biography/Mohammad-Zia-ul-Haq Mohammad Zia-ul-Haq President of Pakistan] on [[Encyclopedia Britannica]]\n* https://ahmadiyyafactcheckblog.com/2019/12/14/did-general-muhammad-zia-ul-haq-join-ahmadiyya-in-the-1940s/\n\n{{s-start}}\n{{s-mil}}\n{{s-bef|before=[[Zulfikar Ali Bhutto]]}}\n{{s-ttl|title=[[Colonel Commandant]] of [[Pakistan Army Armoured Corps|Army Armoured Corps]]|years=1974\u20131978}}\n{{s-aft|after=[[Ali Jan Mehsud]]}}\n|-\n{{s-bef|before=[[Tikka Khan]]}}\n{{s-ttl|title=[[Chief of Army Staff (Pakistan)|Chief of Army Staff]]|years=1976\u20131988}}\n{{s-aft|after=[[Mirza Aslam Beg]]}}\n|-\n{{s-off}}\n{{s-bef|before=[[Zulfikar Ali Bhutto]]}}\n{{s-ttl|title=[[Defence Minister of Pakistan|Minister of Defence]]|years=1978}}\n{{s-aft|after=[[Ali Ahmed Khan Talpur]]}}\n|-\n{{s-bef|before=[[Ali Ahmed Khan Talpur]]}}\n{{s-ttl|title=[[Defenc