\n|subdivision_name = {{flag|Iran}}\n|subdivision_type1 =[[Provinces of Iran|Province]]\n|subdivision_name1 =[[Kermanshah Province|Kermanshah]]\n|subdivision_type2 =[[Counties of Iran|County]]\n|subdivision_name2 = [[Qasr-e Shirin County|Qasr-e Shirin]]\n|subdivision_type3 =[[Bakhsh]]\n|subdivision_name3 =[[Central District (Qasr-e Shirin County)|Central]]\n|subdivision_type4 =[[Rural Districts of Iran|Rural District]]\n|subdivision_name4 =[[Nasrabad Rural District (Kermanshah Province)|Nasrabad]]\n|leader_title           = \n|leader_name            = \n|established_title      =\n|established_date       = \n|area_total_km2           = \n|area_footnotes           = \n|population_as_of         = 2006\n|population_total =405\n|population_density_km2   =auto\n|timezone               = [[Iran Standard Time|IRST]]\n|utc_offset             = +3:30\n|timezone_DST           = [[Iran Daylight Time|IRDT]]\n|utc_offset_DST         = +4:30\n|coordinates            = \n|elevation_m            = \n|area_code              = \n|website                = \n|footnotes              =\n}}\n'''Karak Harak''' ({{lang-fa|\u0643\u0631\u0643\u0647\u0631\u0643}}) is a village in [[Nasrabad Rural District (Kermanshah Province)]], in the [[Central District (Qasr-e Shirin County)|Central District]] of [[Qasr-e Shirin County]], [[Kermanshah Province]], [[Iran]]. At the 2006 census, its population was 405, in 99 families.<ref>{{IranCensus2006|05}}</ref>\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{Qasr-e Shirin County}}\n\n{{coord missing|Kermanshah Province}}\n\n{{Portal|Iran}}\n\n[[Category:Populated places in Qasr-e Shirin County]]\n\n\n{{QasrShirin-geo-stub}}\n", "name_user": "49.195.74.147", "label": "unsafe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Karak_Harak"}
{"title_page": "Periam", "text_new": "{{Infobox Romanian subdivision\n|type                   = commune\n|county                 = Timi\u0219\n|population_total       = auto\n|map_caption            = Location in Timi\u0219 County\n|name=Periam\n|leader_name= Cornel Dumitra\u0219\n|leader_party= PSD\n|image_map              = Periam jud Timis.png\n|area_total_km2          = 64.47\n|coordinates = {{coord|46|3|N|20|52|E|region:RO|display=it}}\n}}\n'''Periam''' ({{lang-hu|Perj\u00e1mos}}) is a [[Commune in Romania|commune]] in [[Timi\u0219 County]], [[Romania]]. It is composed of a single village, Periam, and also included [[Pesac]] until it broke off as a separate commune in 2007.\n\n{{Timi\u0219 County}}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n[[Category:Communes in Timi\u0219 County]]\n[[Category:Localities in Romanian Banat]]\n\n\n{{Timi\u0219-geo-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox Romanian subdivision\n|type                   = commune\n|county                 = Timi\u0219\n|population_total       = auto\n|map_caption            = Location in Timi\u0219 County\n|name=Periam\n|leader_name= Cornel Dumitra\u0219\n|leader_party= [[Social Democratic Party (Romania)|PSD]]\n|image_map=\n|area_total_km2          = 64.47\n|coordinates = {{coord|46|3|N|20|52|E|region:RO|display=it}}\n}}\n'''Periam''' ({{lang-hu|Perj\u00e1mos}}) is a [[Commune in Romania|commune]] in [[Timi\u0219 County]], [[Romania]]. It is composed of a single village, Periam, and also included [[Pesac]] until it broke off as a separate commune in 2007.\n\n{{Timi\u0219 County}}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n[[Category:Communes in Timi\u0219 County]]\n[[Category:Localities in Romanian Banat]]\n\n\n{{Timi\u0219-geo-stub}}\n", "name_user": "Markussep", "label": "safe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Periam"}
{"title_page": "Forbes Korea Power Celebrity", "text_new": "{{short description|Wikimedia list article}}\n{{italic title|string=Forbes}}\n[[File:Forbes logo.svg|thumb]]\n'''''Forbes'' Korea Power Celebrity''' is an annual list published by ''Forbes'' magazine (Korea) since 2010. It is a catalog of the Top 40 Most Powerful Celebrities in South Korea where personalities from sports, music, arts, film and television are ranked according to their professional achievements, influence, popularity and earnings from the past year.<ref name=\"2017 Korea Power Celebrity List\">{{cite web|title=[SPECIAL EDITION (1)] \ubc15\ubcf4\uac80\u00b7\uc1a1\uc911\uae30 \ud55c\uad6d \ucd5c\uace0 \ud30c\uc6cc \uc140\ub7ec\ube0c\ub9ac\ud2f0 |url=http://jmagazine.joins.com/forbes/view/315606|website=Forbes}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Park Bo-gum selected as top celebrity|url=http://kpopherald.koreaherald.com/view.php?ud=201702281734409682757_2|website=Korea Herald}}</ref>\n\n==Top 10 by year==\n===2010===\n[https://www.forbes.com/2010/07/16/celebs-korea-rankings-entertainers-power-asia_slide.html ''Full list of individuals in the 2010 list'']\n[[File:Kim Yu Na David Shankbone 2010 NYC.jpg|thumb|upright|[[Yuna Kim]], figure skater]]\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"width:550px\"\n|-\n! Rank\n! Name\n! Profession\n|-\n| 1\n| [[Yuna Kim]]\n| Figure skater\n|-\n| 2\n| [[Girls' Generation]]\n| Girl group\n|-\n| 3\n| [[Park Ji-sung]]\n| Footballer\n|-\n| 4\n| [[Lee Byung-hun]]\n| Actor\n|-\n| 5\n| [[Big Bang (South Korean band)|Big Bang]]\n| Boy band\n|-\n| 6 \n| | [[Go Hyun-jung]]\n| Actress\n|-\n| 7\n| | [[Lee Seung-gi]]\n| Singer, actor, host\n|-\n| 8\n| | [[Lee Hyo-ri]]\n| Singer\n|-\n| 9\n| [[Yoo Jae-suk]]\n| Host, comedian\n|-\n| 10\n| [[Kang Ho-dong]]\n| Host, comedian\n|-\n|}\n\n===2011===\n[https://www.forbes.com/global/2011/0411/life-park-ji-sung-yuna-kim-2pm-korea-top-celebrities.html ''Full list of individuals in the 2011 list'']\n[[File:SNSD Visual Dream World Premiere Showcase (1).jp