{"title_page": "Emmanuelle Anthoine", "text_new": "{{short description|French politician}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=April 2020}}\n{{infobox officeholder\n| name        = Emmanuelle Anthoine\n| office      = Member of the [[National Assembly (France)|National Assembly]]<br />for Dr\u00f4me's 4th constituency\n| term_start  = 21 June 2017\n| term_end    =\n| predecessor = Nathalie Nieson\n| birth_date  = {{birth date and age|1964|07|02|df=yes}}\n| birth_place = [[Saint-Vallier, Dr\u00f4me|Saint-Vallier]], France\n| nationality = French\n| party       = [[The Republicans (France)|The Republicans]]\n}}\n'''Emmanuelle Anthoine''' (born 2 July 1964) is a French politician of [[The Republicans (France)|the Republicans]] who was elected to the [[National Assembly (France)|French National Assembly]] on 18 June 2017, representing the\n[[Dr\u00f4me's 4th constituency|4th constituency]] of the [[Departments of France|department]] of [[Dr\u00f4me]].<ref name=\"Bio\">{{Cite web|url=http://elections.interieur.gouv.fr/legislatives-2017/026/02604.html |title=Elections l\u00e9gislatives 2017 |accessdate=19 June 2017 |work=Ministry of the Interior |language=French}}</ref>\n\nIn parliament, Anthoine serves on the Committee on Cultural Affairs and Education. In addition to her committee assignments, she is a member of the French-Jordanian Parliamentary Friendship Group.<ref>[http://www2.assemblee-nationale.fr/deputes/fiche/OMC_PA719318 Emmanuelle Anthoine] [[National Assembly (France)|French National Assembly]].</ref>\n\nIn the Republicans' [[2017 The Republicans (France) leadership election|2017 leadership election]], Anthoine endorsed [[Laurent Wauquiez]] as chairman.<ref>Ludovic Vigogne (11 October 2017), [https://www.lopinion.fr/edition/politique/liste-136-parrains-laurent-wauquiez-135723 La liste des 136 parrains de Laurent Wauquiez] ''[[L'Opinion (French newspaper)|L'Opinion]]''.</ref> In the Republicans\u2019 [[2017 The Republicans (France) leadership election|2017 leadership election]], she endorsed [[Laurent Wauquiez]].<ref>Ludovic Vigogne (11 October 2017), [https://www.lopinion.fr/edition/politique/liste-136-parrains-laurent-wauquiez-135723 La liste des 136 parrains de Laurent Wauquiez] ''[[L'Opinion (French newspaper)|L'Opinion]]''.</ref>\n\n==See also==\n* [[2017 French legislative election]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Anthoine, Emmanuelle}}\n[[Category:1964 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Deputies of the 15th National Assembly of the French Fifth Republic]]\n[[Category:The Republicans (France) politicians]]\n[[Category:People from Dr\u00f4me]]\n[[Category:Women members of the National Assembly (France)]]\n[[Category:21st-century French women politicians]]\n\n{{France-politician-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{short description|French politician}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=March 2020}}\n{{infobox officeholder\n| name        = Emmanuelle Anthoine\n| office      = Member of the [[National Assembly (France)|National Assembly]]<br />for Dr\u00f4me's 4th constituency\n| term_start  = 21 June 2017\n| term_end    =\n| predecessor = Nathalie Nieson\n| birth_date  = {{birth date and age|1964|07|02|df=yes}}\n| birth_place = [[Saint-Vallier, Dr\u00f4me|Saint-Vallier]], France\n| nationality = French\n| party       = [[The Republicans (France)|The Republicans]]\n}}\n'''Emmanuelle Anthoine''' (born 2 July 1964) is a French politician of [[The Republicans (France)|the Republicans]] who was elected to the [[National Assembly (France)|French National Assembly]] on 18 June 2017, representing the\n[[Dr\u00f4me's 4th constituency|4th constituency]] of the [[Departments of France|department]] of [[Dr\u00f4me]].<ref name=\"Bio\">{{Cite web|url=http://elections.interieur.gouv.fr/legislatives-2017/026/02604.html |title=Elections l\u00e9gislatives 2017 |accessdate=19 June 2017 |work=Ministry of the Interior |language=French}}</ref>\n\nIn parliament, Anthoine serves on the Committee on Cultural Affairs and Education. In addition to her committee assignments, she is a member of the French-Jordanian Parliamentary Friendship Group.<ref>[http://www2.assemblee-nationale.fr/deputes/fiche/OMC_PA719318 Emmanuelle Anthoine] [[National Assembly (France)|French National Assembly]].</ref>\n\nIn the Republicans' [[2017 The Republicans (France) leadership election|2017 leadership election]], Anthoine endorsed [[Laurent Wauquiez]] as chairman.<ref>Ludovic Vigogne (11 October 2017), [https://www.lopinion.fr/edition/politique/liste-136-parrains-laurent-wauquiez-135723 La liste des 136 parrains de Laurent Wauquiez] ''[[L'Opinion (French newspaper)|L'Opinion]]''.</ref> In the Republicans\u2019 [[2017 The Republicans (France) leadership election|2017 leadership election]], she endorsed [[Laurent Wauquiez]].<ref>Ludovic Vigogne (October 11, 2017), [https://www.lopinion.fr/edition/politique/liste-136-parrains-laurent-wauquiez-135723 La liste des 136 parrains de Laurent Wauquiez] ''[[L'Opinion (French newspaper)|L'Opinion]]''.</ref>\n\n==See also==\n* [[2017 French legislative election]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Anthoine, Emmanuelle}}\n[[Category:1964 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Deputies of the 15th National Assembly of the French Fifth Republic]]\n[[Category:The Republicans (France) politicians]]\n[[Category:People from Dr\u00f4me]]\n[[Category:Women members of the National Assembly (France)]]\n[[Category:21st-century French women politicians]]\n\n{{France-politician-stub}}\n", "name_user": "Lugnuts", "label": "safe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Emmanuelle_Anthoine"}
{"title_page": "Peciu Nou", "text_new": "{{Infobox Romanian subdivision\n|type                   = commune\n|county                 = Timi\u0219\n|population_total       = auto\n|map_caption            = Location in Timi\u0219 County\n|name=Peciu Nou\n|leader_name= Gabriel Dr\u0103gan\n|leader_party= PSD\n|image_map              = Peciu Nou jud Timis.png\n|area_total_km2          = 129.74\n|coordinates = {{coord|45|36|N|21|3|E|region:RO|display=it}}\n}}\n'''Peciu Nou''' ({{lang-de|Neupetsch}} or ''Ulmbach''; {{lang-hu|\u00dajp\u00e9cs}}; {{lang-sr|\u0423\u043b\u0431\u0435\u0447}}) is a [[Commune in Romania|commune]] in [[Timi\u0219 County]], [[Romania]]. It is composed of three villages: Dinia\u0219 (''Toront\u00e1ldinny\u00e9s''; \u0414\u0438\u045a\u0430\u0448), Peciu Nou and S\u00e2nmartinu S\u00e2rbesc (''Szerbszentm\u00e1rton''; \u0421\u0440\u043f\u0441\u043a\u0438 \u0421\u0435\u043c\u0430\u0440\u0442\u043e\u043d).\n\nAt the 2002 census, 75.6% of inhabitants were [[Romanians]], 18.5% [[Serbs]], 2.3% [[Hungarians]], 1.6% [[Ukrainians]], 1.1% [[Germans]] and 0.9% [[Roma in Romania|Roma]]. 87.1% were [[Romanian Orthodox|Romanian]] and [[Serbian Orthodox]], 5.9% [[Pentecostal Union of Romania|Pentecostal]], 3.4% [[Roman Catholic]] and 1.6% [[Romanian Church United with Rome, Greek-Catholic|Greek-Catholic]].\n\n{{Timi\u0219 County}}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n[[Category:Communes in Timi\u0219 County]]\n[[Category:Localities in Romanian Banat]]\n\n\n{{Timi\u0219-geo-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox Romanian subdivision\n|type                   = commune\n|county                 = Timi\u0219\n|population_total       = auto\n|map_caption            = Location in Timi\u0219 County\n|name=Peciu Nou\n|leader_name= Gabriel Dr\u0103gan\n|leader_party= [[Social Democratic Party (Romania)|PSD]]\n|image_map=\n|area_total_km2          = 129.74\n|coordinates = {{coord|45|36|N|21|3|E|region:RO|display=it}}\n}}\n'''Peciu Nou''' ({{lang-de|Neupetsch}} or ''Ulmbach''; {{lang-hu|\u00dajp\u00e9cs}}; {{lang-sr|\u0423\u043b\u0431\u0435\u0447}}) is a [[Commune in Romania|commune]] in [[Timi\u0219 County]], [[Romania]]. It is composed of three villages: Dinia\u0219 (''Toront\u00e1ldinny\u00e9s''; \u0414\u0438\u045a\u0430\u0448), Peciu Nou and S\u00e2nmartinu S\u00e2rbesc (''Szerbszentm\u00e1rton''; \u0421\u0440\u043f\u0441\u043a\u0438 \u0421\u0435\u043c\u0430\u0440\u0442\u043e\u043d).\n\nAt the 2002 census, 75.6% of inhabitants were [[Romanians]], 18.5% [[Serbs]], 2.3% [[Hungarians]], 1.6% [[Ukrainians]], 1.1% [[Germans]] and 0.9% [[Roma in Romania|Roma]]. 87.1% were [[Romanian Orthodox|Romanian]] and [[Serbian Orthodox]], 5.9% [[Pentecostal Union of Romania|Pentecostal]], 3.4% [[Roman Catholic]] and 1.6% [[Romanian Church United with Rome, Greek-Catholic|Greek-Catholic]].\n\n{{Timi\u0219 County}}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n[[Category:Communes in Timi\u0219 County]]\n[[Category:Localities in Romanian Banat]]\n\n\n{{Timi\u0219-geo-stub}}\n", "name_user": "Markussep", "label": "safe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Peciu_Nou"}
